<section class="section-block" data-section-type="problem-solution">
	<h2>What it solves</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>No audio or one-way audio</strong> — Media-path issues often come from NAT, firewall, or RTP pinhole behavior. The appliance gives VoiceTel a controlled path.</li>
		<li><strong>Registration instability</strong> — Keep local PBX registration behavior stable while the appliance handles the upstream secure path.</li>
		<li><strong>Firewall policy friction</strong> — Reduce the need to open broad inbound SIP and RTP exposure at the customer edge.</li>
		<li><strong>Support visibility</strong> — Give support a clearer demarcation point for diagnosing LAN, tunnel, SIP, and media behavior.</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Integrations</h2>
	<p>The SDN appliance is PBX-agnostic and works with any standards-compliant SIP endpoint. See <a href="/support/voice/pbx/">PBX configuration guides</a> for Asterisk, FreePBX, FreeSWITCH, FusionPBX, and 3CX setup, or <a href="/support/voice/sbc/">SBC interop notes</a> for AudioCodes, Cisco CUBE, and FreeSWITCH-as-SBC deployments.</p>
</section>

